<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation assessment">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation assessment.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
EOO (10.195 km2); AOO (8 km2). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Capsicum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capsicum piuranum" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piuranum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Capsicum piuranum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very restricted distribution (EOO and AOO) and a small population size (&lt;250 individuals). This species is proposed as Critically Endangered (CR; C2a(i)) because of the inferred continuing decline in the number of mature individuals in each subpopulation (&lt;50).
</paragraph>
